  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 14.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And during lunch hour, I would buy a newspaper and-- and look at some ads and find that they are looking for hand painters, for artists, whatever, in-- in the Bronx.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then, I would excuse myself under some pretext that I have to visit somebody.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I would go for an interview there and stay there already for the next job.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And come in-- I started in the morning in Bronx and come-- came back home from work from Brooklyn, let's say, and I was pretty-- pretty enterprising in those days.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] And then, of course, when-- when-- when we became engaged and then married, my-- my husband moved from Chicago to New York, together with his parents.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we led a very close family life.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Like, for instance, every weekend was-- we knew we are spending it with our-- after we were married, with our parents.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Whether these were outings.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We bought our first cars, so we used to-- every Sunday, we used to take our parents for a-- a picnic or a-- a trip out-- out of town just to make their life a little bit more pleasant.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We-- for them, they had little difficulties with the new language.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "By that time, we-- we could speak English.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And-- a then the children were born.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And there was a tremendous joys-- joy for us, and of course, for both sets of parents.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We were fortunate that we both had them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I feel-- I find myself extremely fortunate having survived with my mother and being reunited with my parents-- with my father and brother here in the States.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And as a result, maybe I-- I don't-- not that I don't remember, but certain-- certain facts are a little bit blurred.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
